==English==

===Pronunciation===
*chōk, /tʃəʊk/, /<tt>tS@Uk</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-əʊk|Rhymes: -əʊk]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|chok|ing}}

# {{intransitive}}: To be [[unable]] to [[breathe]] because of [[obstruction]] of the [[windpipe]].
# {{transitive}}: To prevent someone from breathing by [[strangling]] them.

====Translations====
'''intransitive''':
*[[Finnish]]: {{trad|fi|tukehtua}}
*[[Kurdish]]: {{trad|ku|fetisîn}}


'''transitive''':
*[[Finnish]]: {{trad|fi|tukehduttaa}}
*[[Kurdish]]: {{trad|ku|fetisandin}}


===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A control on a [[carburettor]] to adjust the [[air]]/[[fuel]] mixture when the engine is cold.
# {{sports}}: In wrestling, karate (etc.), a type of hold that can result in [[strangulation]].
# A constriction at the [[muzzle]] end of a [[shotgun]] [[barrel]] which effects the spread of the [[shot]].

